      <h1>FAQ</h1>

      <section id="attendees">
        <h1>Groups & Attendees</h1>

        <h3>How much are registration fees, when are they due?</h3>
        <p>Early registration fees (Registered before <strong>February 1, 2015</strong>) are $150/person for Youth, Young Adaults, and Chaperones.</p>
        <p>Regular registration fees are $200/person for Youth, Young Adults, and Chaperones.</p>
        <p>As with previous years, for every 5 delegates in your group, a 6th ticket is free.</p>

        <h3>What's up with all the different types of members?</h3>
        <p>Attendees are broken down into 4 different types at Gathering Our Voices. This is a slight change from previous years where there were only 3 types.</p>
        <p>Types of Attendees:
          <div class="label label-info">Y</div> This denotes a Youth, 14-17 years old. These attendees legally require supervision by their chaperones. Up to 5 youth can be in a group per chaperone (or young chaperone!) Youth are generally eligible for most workshops.
          <br>
          <div class="label label-success">YA</div> This denotes a Young Adult, 18-24 years old. These attendees require no supporting chaperones. Young Adults are generally eligible for most workshops.
          <br>
          <div class="label label-warning">YC</div> This denotes a Young Chaperone, 21-24 years old. These attendees are able to support up to 5 youth. Young Chaperones are generally eligible for most workshops.
          <br>
          <div class="label label-danger">Ch</div> This denotes a Chaperone, 24+ years old. These attendees are able to support up to 5 youth. Chaperones are generally only eligible for special workshops.
          <br>
          <div class="label label-default">NA</div> This denotes a member who has not had their type assigned. This generally means the registration system has encountered an error, you're encouraged to edit the attendee and assign them a type.
          <br>
        </p>

        <h3>How do I edit an attendee's information?</h3>
        <p>In the 'Account' page, simply click on their red or green button labelled "Complete" or "Incomplete" in the third column. You should then be able to scroll down and edit their information. On a slow internet connection this may take a few seconds.</p>

        <h3>Who has to register for the conference?</h3>
        <p>All youth and chaperones must register and pay the registration fees for the conference - No Exceptions.</p>

        <h3>What is the Chaperone to Youth Ratio?</h3>
        <p>For every five (5) youth (14-17years) there MUST be at least one (1) chaperone. You MUST be at least Twenty One (21) by March 17, 2014 to be a Chaperone at the conference.</p>

        <h3>How old do you have to be to attend the conference?</h3>
        <p>All youth aged 14-24 are eligible to attend the conference. Youth MUST be fourteen (14) by March 17, 2015 in order to attend.  All youth fourteen to seventeen (14-17) years old MUST be accompanied by a chaperone at all times.</p>
      </section>

